      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It sounds like your symptoms might not be solely due to dry eyes from screen time. Given the redness, discomfort, and discharge, it could be a sign of an infection like conjunctivitis. I would recommend you to consult with a healthcare provider for proper diagnosis and treatment rather than relying solely on over-the-counter drops. They may prescribe specific eye drops that address the root cause of your symptoms. In the meantime, avoid touching or rubbing your eyes, and make sure to wash your hands regularly.",
