      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Even though over-the-counter lubricating eye drops can provide temporary relief for dry eyes, your symptoms of redness, pain, and yellow discharge suggest that your condition is more than just screen-related dry eyes. These symptoms could potentially worsen without proper treatment. Using lubricating drops might only provide temporary relief, but it doesn't address the underlying issue, which could lead to more serious complications and longer recovery time. I strongly recommend postponing the idea of self-medicating with lubricating drops until you can see a healthcare professional who can give you the appropriate treatment and ensure your eyes are okay. It's important to take care of your health despite your busy schedule. Temporary measures should not replace professional medical evaluation and treatment when necessary.",
